    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-09-04T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-09-04T11:00:00-05:00" n="37"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">467n11/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jerusalem</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-04T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 4, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 5—12:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consular corps today requested High Commissioner to take into consideration the
                    question of indemnification for damages suffered by foreigners as a result of
                    the recent disturbances and to inform it of the procedure to be followed in the
                    verification of the damages and in the presentation of claims.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
